President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Christopher E. O'Connor as the Assistant Secretary for Congressional and Legislative Affairs at the Department of Veterans Affairs. He also announced his intent to appoint Tamara L. Lundgren, Inge G. Thulin, Naseem Kourosh, Barbara Satin, Manjit Singh, Jack Martin Brandt, Dan Habib, Michelle C. Reynolds, Ricardo Thornton, Sr., Rev. Thomas J. Reese, S.J., and Dr. John Ruskay to various advisory committees and councils. Each individual has a strong background and experience in their respective fields. President Obama expressed his confidence in their abilities and looks forward to working with them.